<br>
With friends this is fairly easy, we do it one person loots everything, split in the end, valuable item drops are amiably agreed upon, if two really want the same item roll.<br>
<br>
If strangers come into the group, we ask them what they want (money/exp/loot) and if they are ok with Master loot. If not, we let them loot every nth (for example 5th if they join in a group of 4 friends) mob with autosplit off. We never pull NBG on strangers, since they can sell the item or trade it for an item they need most times, if it is valuable. With strangers, any and all valuable items are rolled on, highest gets to keep it, out on the same item until all have one, but not on other valuable ones. Oftentimes stangers are nice enough to let the item go to someone who needs it if they win, as are we if we win something we cannot use but they can, but that is purely voluntary. No drop items obvioulsy are only rolled on by people that need them. And if we REALLY REALLY want a certain item for one of us, we either will not let strangers join at all or tell them before joining that item A is reserved for person B in case it drops and they are only welcome to join if that is fine with them.<br>
<br>
No one complained about this so far.<br>
